%sh
pip install kafka-python
cd /zeppelin && wget https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/spark/spark-streaming-kafka-0-8-assembly_2.11/2.0.2/spark-streaming-kafka-0-8-assembly_2.11-2.0.2.jar && ls /zeppelin

%producer.pyspark
import time
import json
import random
import logging

from kafka import KafkaProducer
from kafka.errors import KafkaError

KAFKA_BROKER = "host.docker.internal:9092"
KAFKA_TOPIC = "logins"

producer = KafkaProducer(bootstrap_servers=[KAFKA_BROKER])
index = 0

while True:
    
    row_dict = record(time.time())
    
    future = producer.send(
        topic=KAFKA_TOPIC, 
        key=str(row_dict["id"]).encode("utf-8"),
        value=json.dumps(row_dict).encode("utf-8"))
    
    try:
        record_metadata = future.get(timeout=10)
    except KafkaError:
        # Decide what to do if produce request failed...
        logging.exception("Error")
        pass
    
    producer.flush()
    
    index += 1
    time.sleep(random.uniform(0.1,3.0))

%spark.pyspark

import json
from pyspark.streaming.kafka import KafkaUtils
from pyspark.streaming import StreamingContext
import os
# os.environ['PYSPARK_SUBMIT_ARGS'] = '--jars /zeppelin/spark-streaming-kafka-0-8-assembly_2.11-2.0.2.jar pyspark-shell' 

try:
    # Reset streaming context if exists
    ssc.stop(stopSparkContext=False, stopGraceFully=False)
except:
    pass

ssc = StreamingContext(sc, batchDuration=2)

LOGINS_TOPIC = "logins"
KAFKA_BROKERS = "host.docker.internal:9092,host.docker.internal:9092"

stream = KafkaUtils.createDirectStream(
                            ssc, 
                            [LOGINS_TOPIC], 
                            {"metadata.broker.list": KAFKA_BROKERS})

stream = stream.map(lambda x: json.loads(x[1]))
stream = stream.map(lambda x: (x["id"], x["data"]))

stream.pprint()

ssc.start()
ssc.awaitTermination()
